aise the life force between the eyebrows (to the \u003cem\u003eājñā-cakra\u003c/em\u003e). The practice of \u003cem\u003eṣaṭ-cakra-yoga,\u003c/em\u003e involving meditation on the six \u003cem\u003ecakras,\u003c/em\u003e is suggested here. A pure devotee does not practice such \u003cem\u003eyoga,\u003c/em\u003e but because he is always engaged in Kṛṣṇa consciousness, at death he can remember the Supreme Personality of Godhead by His grace. This is explained in verse 14.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2419,\"bb\":2145,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/10/b2145/\",\"body_value\":\"The particular use of the word \u003cem\u003eyoga-balena\u003c/em\u003e is significant in this verse because without practice of \u003cem\u003eyoga\u003c/em\u003e – whether \u003cem\u003eṣaṭ-cakra-yoga\u003c/em\u003e or \u003cem\u003ebhakti-yoga\u003c/em\u003e – one cannot come to this transcendental state of being at the time of death. One cannot suddenly remember the Supreme Lord at death; one must have practiced some \u003cem\u003eyoga\u003c/em\u003e system, especially the system of \u003cem\u003ebhakti-yoga.\u003c/em\u003e Since one’s mind at death is very disturbed, one should practice transcendence through \u003cem\u003eyoga\u003c/em\u003e during one’s life.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 8.10\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 8.10\"},{\"id\":2420,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"11\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 11\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/advanced-view/#bb2146\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/8/11/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url