ṣye\u003c/em\u003e\"}]},{\"section\":\"synonyms\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.synonyms\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"books.Synonyms\",\"title\":\"synonyms\",\"id\":2423,\"bb\":2148,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/11/b2148/\",\"shadow_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eyat\u003c/em\u003e – that which; \u003cem\u003eakṣaram\u003c/em\u003e – syllable \u003cem\u003eoṁ;\u003c/em\u003e \u003cem\u003eveda-vidaḥ\u003c/em\u003e – persons conversant with the \u003cem\u003eVedas;\u003c/em\u003e \u003cem\u003evadanti\u003c/em\u003e – say; \u003cem\u003eviśanti\u003c/em\u003e – enter; \u003cem\u003eyat\u003c/em\u003e – in which; \u003cem\u003eyatayaḥ\u003c/em\u003e – great sages; \u003cem\u003evīta-rāgāḥ\u003c/em\u003e – in the renounced order of life; \u003cem\u003eyat\u003c/em\u003e – that which; \u003cem\u003eicchantaḥ\u003c/em\u003e – desiring; \u003cem\u003ebrahma-caryam\u003c/em\u003e – celibacy; \u003cem\u003ecaranti\u003c/em\u003e – practice; \u003cem\u003etat\u003c/em\u003e – that; \u003cem\u003ete\u003c/em\u003e – unto you; \u003cem\u003epadam\u003c/em\u003e – situation; \u003cem\u003esaṅgraheṇa\u003c/em\u003e – in summary; \u003cem\u003epravakṣye\u003c/em\u003e – I shall explain.\",\"word_for_word_value\":[{\"word\":\"yat\",\"translation\":\"that which\"},{\"word\":\"akṣaram\",\"translation\":\"syllable \u003cem\u003eoṁ\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"word\":\"veda-vidaḥ\",\"translation\":\"persons conversant with the \u003cem\u003eVedas\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"word\":\"vadanti\",\"translation\":\"say\"},{\"word\":\"viśanti\",\"translation\":\"enter\"},{\"word\":\"yat\",\"translation\":\"in which\"},{\"word\":\"yatayaḥ\",\"translation\":\"great sages\"},{\"word\":\"vīta-rāgāḥ\",\"translation\":\"in the renounced order of life\"},{\"word\":\"yat\",\"translation\":\"that which\"},{\"word\":\"icchantaḥ\",\"translation\":\"desiring\"},{\"word\":\"brahma-caryam\",\"translation\":\"celibacy\"},{\"word\":\"caranti\",\"translation\":\"practice\"},{\"word\":\"tat\",\"translation\":\"that\"},{\"word\