levated to higher and higher planets and at the time of universal devastation are transferred to the eternal spiritual kingdom. Baladeva Vidyābhūṣaṇa, in his commentary on \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā,\u003c/em\u003e quotes this verse:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":2460,\"bb\":2180,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/16/b2180/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003ebrahmaṇā saha te sarve\u003cbr /\u003esamprāpte pratisañcare\u003cbr /\u003eparasyānte kṛtātmānaḥ\u003cbr /\u003epraviśanti paraṁ padam\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2461,\"bb\":2181,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/16/b2181/\",\"body_value\":\"“When there is devastation of this material universe, Brahmā and his devotees, who are constantly engaged in Kṛṣṇa consciousness, are all transferred to the spiritual universe and to specific spiritual planets according to their desires.”\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 8.16\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 8.16\"},{\"id\":2462,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"17\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 17\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/advanced-view/#bb2182\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/8/17/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/8/17/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/8/17/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/8/17/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/libr