 beg alms from door to door and bring them to the spiritual master. He takes food only under the master’s order, and if the master neglects to call the student for food that day, the student fasts. These are some of the Vedic principles for observing \u003cem\u003ebrahmacarya.\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2537,\"bb\":2245,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/28/b2245/\",\"body_value\":\"$3c\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2538,\"bb\":2246,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/28/b2246/\",\"body_value\":\"The beauty of Kṛṣṇa consciousness, however, is that by one stroke, by engaging in devotional service, one can surpass all the rituals of the different orders of life.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2539,\"bb\":2247,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/28/b2247/\",\"body_value\":\"The words \u003cem\u003eidaṁ viditvā\u003c/em\u003e indicate that one should understand the instructions given by Śrī Kṛṣṇa in this chapter and the Seventh Chapter of \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā.\u003c/em\u003e One should try to understand these chapters not by scholarship or mental speculation but by hearing them in association with devotees. Chapters Seven through Twelve are the essence of \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā.\u003c/em\u003e The first six and the last six chapters are like coverings for the middle six chapters, which are especially protected by the Lord. If one is fortunate enough to understand \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā\u003c/em\u003e – especially these middle six chapters – in the association of devotees, then his life at once becomes glorified beyond all penances, sacrifices, charities, speculations, etc., for one can achieve all the results of these activities simply by Kṛṣṇa consciousness.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2540,\"bb\":2248,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/28/b2248/\",\"body_value\":\"$3d\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph_end\",\"id\":2541,\"bb\":2249,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/8/28/b2249/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eThus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Eighth Chapter of the\u003c/em\u003e Śrīmad Bhagavad-gītā\u003cem\u003e in the matter of Attaining the Supreme.\u003c/em\u003e \"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 8.28\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 8.28\"}]}]},\"locale\":\"en\",\"activeView\":\"$13:props:activeView\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"px-4 py-4 w-full max-w-screen-xl mx-auto md:px-8 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"breadcrumb mb-8 text-base\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/en/library/\",{\"className\":\"inline\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L29\",null,{\"href\":\"/en/library/\",\"className\":\"text-vb-link\",\"children\":\"Library\"}],\" » \"]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/en/library/bg/\",{\"className\":\"inline\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L29\",null,{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/\",\"className\":\"text-vb-link\",\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is\"}],false]}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"children\":[\"$L3e\",[\"$\",\"$L3f\",null,{\"presentSections\":[\"av-verses\",\"av-devanagari\",\"av-verse_text\",\"av-synonyms\",\"av-translation\",\"av-purport\"],\"defaultSettings\":\"$@40\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L41\",null,{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page\",\"hasId\":false,\"isWholePage\":true,\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:text-xl em:mt-3 em:mb-2\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"Chapter Eight\"}}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-4xl em:mb-4 font-bold\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"Attaining the Supreme\"}}]]}],[[\"$\",\"div\",\"section-verses\",{\"className\":\"av-verses\",\"children\":[false,[[\"$\",\"div\",\"child-2351\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L41\",null,{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":fal