s meditation on the Supersoul within; similarly, by chanting Hare Kṛṣṇa one fixes his mind always on the Supreme Lord. The mind is fickle, and therefore it is necessary to engage the mind by force to think of Kṛṣṇa. One example often given is that of the caterpillar that thinks of becoming a butterfly and so is transformed into a butterfly in the same life. Similarly, if we constantly think of Kṛṣṇa, it is certain that at the end of our lives we shall have the same bodily constitution as Kṛṣṇa.\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"6a:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2407-devanagari,2407-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-2408\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:8:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"कविं पुराणमनुशासितार-\u003cbr/\u003eमणोरणीयांसमनुस्मरेद्य: ।\u003cbr/\u003eसर्वस्य धातारमचिन्त्यरूप-\u003cbr/\u003eमादित्यवर्णं तमस: परस्तात् ॥ ९ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\n6b:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2407-verse_text,2407-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-2409\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:8:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003ekaviṁ purāṇam anuśāsitāram\u003cbr /\u003eaṇor aṇīyāṁsam anusmared yaḥ\u003cbr /\u003esarvasya dhātāram acintya-rūpam\u003cbr /\u003eāditya-varṇaṁ tamasaḥ parastāt\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><scri